AWS Parallel Cluster

step-1 Create an ec2 ubuntu Instance with Pre-requisites Installed through CFT
       
step-2 verify the following in the ec2 instance which got created in step-1
       pcluster version
	   node --version
	   aws --version
step-3 clone the git repo which includes cluster.sh
       git clone https://github.com/deepashre/Parallel-Cluster.git
step-4 sudo chmod +x Parallel-Cluster/cluster.sh
step-5 Provide your aws credentials
       aws configure
	   pass the AWS Access Key ID,AWS Secret Access Key,Default region name
step-6 execute the shell script 
       Parallel-Cluster/cluster.sh
step-7 Provide user inputs while 1st stack is getting created as part of the shell script
